main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted by an F-94B pilot of the 59th Fighter-Interceptor Squadron at Goose Air Base, Labrador on 26 November 1952.
interesting points: The sighting lasted 25 minutes,An altitude range of the object was between 1500 to 20,000 feet,The object displayed excellent maneuverability and maintained distance from the F-94B during attempted intercepts,Ground radar had momentary contact with the object but no visual contact was established,The object was concluded to be either an astronomical body or possibly a radar malfunction.
sighted object: unidentified flying object with bright red and white color
witness description: United States Air Force pilots including Captain E. W. Johnson and Lt. M. S. Morris
